cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY

The paper proposes a probabilistic model for the process of learners posting on discussion forums in MOOCs, which involves topic modeling, timescale modeling, and learner topic interest modeling. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computer science and game theory (cs.CY). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories, as they are directly related to the proposed model's core components.
